carldjennings wrote:As a former Navy Electrician, my first though is redundancy. Is the Operations room duplicated somewhere else, in case this room is taken out by enemy fire? Seems like a lot to put in one place without any kind of backup system.The CDS consoles are also on the bridge. There's heavy redundancy of power and network to the ops center. But yes, if the Ops Center is taken out, the ship's weapons capability is offline. Of course, if the ops center is hit, the focus will be on getting the ship out of harms way anyway—and the ship's navigation and control systems can be operated from elsewhere.
