Posted: Fri Oct 18, 2013 10:15 am
Nijyo wrote:This sounds pretty neat and all, but did anyone else start thinking of this baby about half-way through the technical descriptions?:Oh, I thought of starships as soon as I saw the CO's name. Minor nitpick: that's USS Excelsior, which in Trek lore is an experimental ship (notice the NX registry -- X denotes an experimental design just as in the modern Navy) and the first of her class. A ship of that design was later named Enterprise and appeared in a later movie (Generations) -- that shot is from Star Trek III. The Enterprise did not have the experimental propulsion system that Excelsior had -- it turned out to be impractical and the complexity wasn't worth the benefit.It's not unlike how a 1/4 scale model of the tumblehome design was built to ascertain whether it would be seaworthy.https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sea_JetFrom a distance, these ships don't look like what we'd expect ships to look like, since the design's been out of use for so long. The Sea Jet actually showed up on a cryptid website:http://www.cryptomundo.com/cryptozoo-news/paddler-pic/ (lower right).
